cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR

This paper deals with deep neural networks and their interpretation, specifically in the context of medical image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of traditional approaches and known operators, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep networks and their optimization could also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of trained layers using signal processing tools, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
